.TH LIBREPODS-CTL 1 "April 2026" "linuxpods 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
librepods-ctl \- command-line control tool for LinuxPods
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B librepods-ctl
.I COMMAND
.RI [ ARGS... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B librepods-ctl
is a small command-line client that talks to a running
.BR linuxpods-daemon (1)
over D-Bus. It is intended for scripting, debugging and headless use
where neither the standalone
.BR librepods (1)
GUI nor the Plasma 6 widget are available.
.PP
All commands operate on the currently-connected AirPods device.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Print the current device name, battery levels (left earbud, right
earbud, case), noise-control mode, and ear-detection state.
.TP
.B noise \fIMODE\fR
Set the noise-control mode. \fIMODE\fR must be one of
.BR off ,
.BR anc ,
.BR transparency ,
or
.BR adaptive .
.TP
.B ca \fBon\fR|\fBoff\fR
Enable or disable Conversational Awareness.
.TP
.B battery
Print battery levels as machine-readable \fIkey=value\fR lines.
.TP
.B connect
Attempt to (re)connect to the last-known device.
.TP
.B disconnect
Disconnect from the current device.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B librepods-ctl
exits with status 0 on success and non-zero on failure (no device, D-Bus
error, invalid argument).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR linuxpods-daemon (1),
.BR librepods (1),
.BR busctl (1)
.SH BUGS
Report issues at
.UR https://github.com/Explor3Universe/LinuxPods/issues
.UE .
